      <heading>Sat May 25 (Amarinda)   :: &amp;WPop Quiz!&amp;n</heading>
      <slot>1</slot>
      <level>210</level>
      <author>0</author>
      <date>0</date>
      <text>I'm guessing that you guys have seen my post on the imm board by now so
I'm going to skip all the introductory stuff for now. If you have any
questions at all, please please please come to me. We can't work anything
out if you don't speak up and we all have opinions - however hard we try
to bite them back.

Now, the quiz. It's not necessarily a quiz, but we've all been here long
enough to know what should and shouldn't be done as well as how to work
with people that aren't level 203 - and you need to. I want to be dead
sure that everyone that is GL of a guild knows about this little thing
called policy. Also, something that you need to read if you haven't for
some odd reason - handbook. Yes, we all come here to have fun and I want
you guys to have as much fun as everyone else but the point is, you've
hired on to do a job and I'm going to expect it done. I don't think that's
unreasonable. I know some will and that's, well, it's sad.

I expect you all to put in decent time and energy into your guild and work
with your guildies. If something is bothering you, come to me. Chances are
I'm going to listen and understand where you're coming from. Try me. If
you're having a bad day and don't want to spend an hour on a help file then
by all means, log on a mort and roleplay, level, do what you want to do.
It's much better for you to log off your imm if you're not wanting to handle
issues than to sit around and idle watching the screen scroll with tells
because you can't be bothered. I'm not saying that in order to have fun with
an alt that you have to log off your imm, but if you leave your imm on, then
answer those tells, listen to your channels, be responsive. I feel the need
to say again - don't neglect the guild but take time out to have a little
fun. However, if you've done nothing productive for two weeks or it takes
you that long to respond to mails - it might be a little more difficult to
keep a spotlight position.

I will be talking to all of you as the chances come available. Don't wait
for it though, come to me if you want something. If I don't respond within
a day of a mail, send me a tell. If you need things done then make me do
them. If you are having a helluva arguement with someone let me know so
I can be there and try to help with it.

So, like I said, not much of a quiz but everyone needs to be familiar with
the basics again because it's expected. Not much more of a chance to sit
around and do nothing or abuse powers. Anyone noticed the lack of faith
in the immortals? Even those that have been working their arses off? Think
we should fix that? I damn sure do.
</text>
    </message>
