      <text>Hm. Changes made and we're all still alive. Damn skippy!

A few thoughts now that most of the tedious stuff is complete. First, you
have all done a great deal to make this work and I do hope that continues.
We have bumps in the road but at least it wasn't trees. You've all offered
a great deal of feedback and that is important. It's now your turn to get
out and about and get feedback for yourself.

As you know, I'm altering the job description. However, after thinking on
this for two days, I've discovered something. We each define our jobs in
our own way and bring something unique to it. I'm going to describe a bit
of what I want or what I would like to see and then we'll discuss what it
is that you are actually doing. Everyone will be doing things their way
and I think a mix and match is important. I know the morts get a different
answer from each of us when asked about what's going on. Let's see what
happens next.

I'd like to say that most changes are complete and it's time to start a
new path. That being getting out with the mortals and being players
-with- them. We are players. We have a high level to help them. While
there are a few perks, that's what it boils down to. Yeah, I'll quit
saying this eventually, but I think it's a hot topic right now. I am
going to start looking for you out with the population and working. If
you have quest ideas, post them on the quest board. Or just ideas in
general.

Mortal Guild Leaders:
If you have questions about what you need to be doing, talk with the imm
in charge of the group or myself. You are responsible for the majority of
stuff now.

*wanders off*
</text>
