      <text>
I've noticed a trend recently (or actually, noticed it cropping up again)
where if a seeker is trying to get something ludicrous approved and is
told no, they just smile and nod and go down the line and ask the next
person who might be able to approve their BG. Of course, the never mention
that they've already been turned down. This further supports what Amarinda
says about us having to work together. Also, I'm personally in favor of
upping the ante in terms of strict judging of BGs for anyone who tries this
stunt. There are a lot of iffy things we let slide through on a BG, but if
someone tries the ridiculous and is told no and tries to get someone else
to approve it instead, we should disallow anything even remotely grayish
in any BG they ever propose from that moment on. IMO.
</text>
