      <header>Inactivity</header>
      <slot>13</slot>
      <level>210</level>
      <author>243260</author>
      <date>1058064141</date>
      <authorname>Amarinda</authorname>
      <text>It seems activity has dwindled down to very little and in times like this,
there's always the question of what to do about those in our ranks that
never show up.

The answer is not to deguild them. If you feel that you simply have to do
something with the inactive players, then tag them as inactive. There is
a reason that the guilded pfiles are deleted after a longer amount of time
than the unguilded. And likely, it's just going to create more work for
you in the end. They log in, have to have their character revived, then
they want to be reguilded. You have to look around for whatever rank they
had or take them at their word, and all the stuff that goes with that.

That said, I don't want inactives deguilded. Leave them there. Mark them
how you want, but it's pointless to deguild them and have them deleted.
It's simply a bad idea all the way around.
</text>
    </message>
