      <authorname>Amarinda</authorname>
      <text>Let me try this again.

Our playerbase has been low and slow this summer. That is not a reason
to slack off on work and such. If anything, it's the best time to get
stuff done because you don't have someone nagging you for something
constantly. It's -our- job to get people here and active and interested.
Think you can do your part? Go IC and get roleplay started, do a quest,
do behind the scenes stuff, but do -something-. If you don't want to do
anything and you want to stand around, quit being an immortal. If you
don't want to handle requests and get people interested in your guild,
give up the position so that someone else can try. This whole apathetic
approach to stuff that I'm seeing is about to result in a lot of hurt
feelings because it's time to get over it. If you literally have nothing
to do, see one of the department heads because there are a lot of things
that could and should be resolved. There -is- work enough to go around.

Amarinda
