      <text>In case you haven't noticed, there have been some changes made with the
immortals.  Before, they were told to define their own jobs.  Well, now
I'M defining them.  

ImmGLs will have the same responsibilities and authority as MortGLs once
more.  This includes things like handling seekers, aka approving
applications and/or helping to make the application workable, guilding,
explaining things, like promoting people, reviewing RP logs, settling
disputes, etc.  This isn't rocket science; most of this is obvious.  You
will be working as a team with your MortGL, assuming the guild has one, so
though you should be keeping them in the loop and getting their input,
both you and they should be doing things like scheduling guild RP, guild
activies, et cetra.  Major things like rewriting syllabi/ranking systems
should be done WITH the MortGL.  I EXPECT to see you doing these things.

Any questions, complaints, comments, direct'em my way.
-J
