all to be using it.  No more mailing sponsorships in, no more guilding
without sponsors, and especially, no more guilding without the person(s)
even seeking.  The point of sponsoring is to introduce the seeking
character to the IC world, so this is especially vital with newbies.    

This means: you're going to have to take a more active role in your guild.
Before any of this, you need to check your seeking list, and deguild
anyone who's stopped playing.  Anyone who hasn't, you need to help them
find some RP.  If you can't find any guild members, then you'll have to do
the RP with them yourself.  I promise you, this won't kill you.  =p

